text: Ooo, that's tempting
What percentage of the nonland cards of a deck needs to be on-theme for a deck to be considered to have that theme?
I'd say 75
Murmurs is so good. I remember finding out about it in this Slack, and immediately slotting it into some decks.
Typically I count spirit and things like norn as being ok outside of that
The more you stick to the theme, the more unique your deck and the less opportunity for 'goodstuff'.
I know this is a big point for Dana too. When Jimmy played his Intet Dragon tribal deck and went Sakura Tribe Elder into Oracle of Mul Daya into Eternal witness and it was like :face_with_monocle:
I'm with him...
The more goodstuff you allow, the weaker the theme. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯
I allow a couple cards that are sometimes needed but I try to keep it to a minimum
just be careful about your criteria for 'needed'.
I count like ewit, steve, sometimes norn depending on the context and regrowth in that vein
I'm not playing tireless tracker in a dragon deck for instance
But what if he's tirelessly tracking dragons?!
Well that would be the exception where she would be fine there haha
I'm thinking about 'activated ability tribal' for Ghave where the rule is every permanent must have an activated ability, so Steve would be fine, but not Phyrexian Arena, ewit, etc.
I'm free to include whatever instants and sorceries I want there, but hard and fast on the permanents.
Interesting, that's really cool
That sounds like a sweet deck
When I was running Odric soldiers, I had to supplement it with elesh norn, sun titan and Zetalpa to really have closing power but generally I try to limit that as much as possible
